    "minides": "Retro-futuristic design meets flagship EV tech — the Ioniq 5 facelift redefines what an electric SUV can be.",
    "description": "The Hyundai Ioniq 5 facelift (2026) is launched in India at ₹55.70 lakh (ex-showroom). It is powered by an 84 kWh battery with a single PMS motor producing 225 bhp, offering a claimed ARAI range of 690 km. It supports 350 kW DC fast charging (10–80% in 18 minutes) and 11 kW AC charging. Features include dual 12.3-inch screens, 8-way powered driver's seat, wireless Android Auto & Apple CarPlay, dual-zone climate control, 8 airbags, Level 2 ADAS, OTA updates, Remote Smart Parking Assist 2 (RSPA2), Blind-Spot Collision Avoidance, and V2L (Vehicle-to-Load) capability. Available in a single RWD variant."
